Clinical studies have shown that affected individuals hyperabsorb all dietary sterols ( thus have lost the ability to restrict the sterol species <termsem="GO:0050892"> absorbed </term> ) and have lost the ability to <termsem="GO:0046903"> excrete </term> sterols into bile [ 8,9 ] .
